  <!-- FORMBY PROPERTY KNOWLEDGE - UNIQUE SECTION -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pf-section-label">LOCAL EXPERTISE</span>
      <h2>Formby Properties. What Our Engineers Find.</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Formby is one of Merseyside's most affluent residential areas. The properties here are larger, the systems are more complex, and when something goes wrong at 11pm, you need an engineer who knows what they are looking at.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">L37</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Executive Homes with Multi-Bathroom Systems</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Formby's larger detached and semi-detached properties frequently have three or more bathrooms, complex pressurised heating systems and unvented hot water cylinders. When a fault develops in a multi-bathroom property, the consequences are more significant than a simple single-bathroom terrace. A leaking cylinder or failed pump can affect water supply and heating throughout a large house very quickly. Our engineers hold G3 qualifications for unvented cylinder work and are fully equipped to diagnose and repair complex multi-zone heating systems. We attend properties across Formby's private estates regularly and carry appropriate stock for high-spec plumbing systems.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">FRESHFIELD</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">The Pine Roads and Period Properties</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Freshfield contains some of Formby's most distinctive period housing, including the well-known Pine Roads area with its National Trust surroundings. Properties here range from substantial Edwardian and inter-war houses to 1960s and 1970s bungalows. The bungalow stock in Freshfield is particularly prone to frozen pipe issues in cold weather because the pipework runs in loft spaces directly beneath exposed roof sections with minimal insulation in some cases. We regularly attend Freshfield properties for both emergency call-outs and planned work and understand the variety of property types in this part of L37.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">COASTAL</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Sandy Ground and Coastal Conditions</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Formby sits on the Lancashire coastal plain and the sandy soil substrate means that ground movement is more common than in clay-heavy inland areas. This can put stress on underground pipe joints and connections over time, leading to gradual leaks that eventually become emergencies. The proximity to the Irish Sea also brings salt-laden air that accelerates corrosion on any external pipework, outdoor taps and exposed fittings. Properties closest to the dune system and beach areas at Formby Point see this most markedly. We have experience identifying and resolving both ground movement related pipe failures and salt corrosion issues specific to Formby's coastal location.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">HIGHTOWN</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Hightown and Ince Blundell</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">The villages south of Formby, including Hightown and Ince Blundell, have a mix of older village properties and newer private developments. Hightown in particular has a number of older properties along the coastal road where external pipework has been subject to decades of marine air exposure. These villages are quieter and more sparsely populated than Formby itself, which means that when a plumbing emergency occurs late at night, you need to be confident your plumber will actually arrive. We attend Hightown and Ince Blundell at any hour, 365 days a year, at the same rates as everywhere else.</p>
