  <!-- COMMON JOBS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Common Emergencies We Fix Across Formby</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">The plumbing faults we attend most frequently across L37, Freshfield, Hightown and surrounding Sefton coast villages.</p>
      <div class="jobs-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="job-card"><h3>Burst Pipes and Water Damage</h3><div class="job-meta"><span class="job-price">£120 to £350</span><span class="job-time">30 to 90 mins</span></div><p>In a large Formby property, a burst pipe can cause significant water damage quickly across multiple floors. The faster we get there, the less damage is done. That is why our 30 minute response matters. We stop the leak, assess the damage and repair or replace the affected section on the first visit.</p></div>
        <div class="job-card"><h3>No Hot Water and Boiler Breakdown</h3><div class="job-meta"><span class="job-price">£150 to £500</span><span class="job-time">45 to 120 mins</span></div><p>Formby properties commonly have high-efficiency condensing boilers and unvented cylinder systems. When these fail, you lose hot water across the whole house instantly. We diagnose and repair on the same visit with parts from the van. Gas Safe engineers only on all boiler work in L37.</p></div>
        <div class="job-card"><h3>Unvented Cylinder Failures</h3><div class="job-meta"><span class="job-price">£150 to £500</span><span class="job-time">60 to 120 mins</span></div><p>Unvented cylinders are common in larger Formby homes and require G3 qualified engineers. When a pressure relief valve fails, an expansion vessel needs replacing, or a thermostat fails, only a G3 qualified engineer can legally carry out the repair. All our engineers hold this qualification.</p></div>
        <div class="job-card job-card--warning"><h3>Gas Leaks</h3><div class="job-meta"><span class="job-price">FREE safety visit</span><span class="job-time">Priority response</span></div><p>If you smell gas at your Formby property, get out immediately and call <a href="https://cadentgas.com/gas-escapes" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="font-weight:700;">Cadent Gas on 0800 111 999</a> first, then call us. Our first gas safety make-safe visit is FREE. Gas Safe registered engineers only.</p></div>
        <div class="job-card"><h3>Blocked Drains and Toilets</h3><div class="job-meta"><span class="job-price">£80 to £250</span><span class="job-time">30 to 90 mins</span></div><p>Drain blockages in sandy Formby ground can sometimes involve root ingress from the mature trees that line many of the area's residential roads. Stop flushing and call us. We use professional clearing equipment and identify the underlying cause to prevent a quick recurrence.</p></div>
        <div class="job-card"><h3>Heating System Failures</h3><div class="job-meta"><span class="job-price">£120 to £350</span><span class="job-time">60 to 120 mins</span></div><p>Multi-zone heating systems in larger Formby properties are more complex to diagnose than a standard single-zone setup. Motorised valves, zone controllers, pumps and thermostats all contribute to these systems. We carry diagnostic equipment and the most common replacement components for these configurations on every van.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ALL FORMBY SERVICES -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">All Plumbing and Heating Services Across Formby</h2>
